1 Write a Java program that uses a while loop to print all the even numbers between 1 and 20


import java.util.*;
public class Main
{
    public static void main(String[] args)
{
        int i = 2; 

       
        while (i <= 20) 
{
            System.out.println(i);
            i += 2; 
        }
    }
}




 2. do-while loop program where the user inputs a range, and the program prints all even numbers between 1 and that range

import java.util.Scanner;
public class Main
{
    public static void main(String[] args)
{
        Scanner scanner = new Scanner(System.in);

        System.out.print("Enter the ending number: ");

        int end = scanner.nextInt();

        int i = 2;
        do{
            System.out.println(i);
            i += 2;
        } 
while (i <= end);
    }
}



3.for loop to calculate the sum of all numbers from 1 to a user-specified number

import java.util.Scanner;

public class Main
{
    public static void main(String[] args)
{
        Scanner scanner = new Scanner(System.in);
        System.out.print("Enter the ending number: ");
        int end = scanner.nextInt();

        for (int i = 2; i <= end; i += 2)
        {
            System.out.println(i);
        }

        
    }
}


4. all three types of loops: for, while, and do-while, to perform the same task â€” printing the even numbers from 1 to a user-specified number.

import java.util.Scanner;
public class Main
{
    public static void main(String[] args) 
{
        Scanner scanner = new Scanner(System.in);
        System.out.print("Enter the ending number: ");
        int end = scanner.nextInt();

        System.out.println("Using for loop:");

        for (int i = 2; i <= end; i += 2) 
        {
            System.out.println(i);
        }

        
        System.out.println("Using while loop:");
        int i = 2;
        while (i <= end) 
        {
            System.out.println(i);
            i += 2;
        }

        
        System.out.println("Using do-while loop:");
        i = 2;
        do {
            System.out.println(i);
            i += 2;
        }
            while (i <= end);

       
    }
}
